{"title_page": "Day of the Idiots", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Day of the Idiots\n| image          = DayoftheIdiots.jpg\n| caption        = Screenshot of Carole Bouquet\n| director       = [[Werner Schroeter]] \n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Karel Dirka]]|[[Peter Gen\u00e9e]]|[[Harald K\u00fcgler]]}}\n| writer         = {{ubl|[[Dana Horakov\u00e1]]|[[Werner Schroeter]]}}\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Carole Bouquet]]|[[Ingrid Caven]]|[[Christine Kaufmann]]}}\n| music          = [[Peer Raben]]\n| cinematography = [[Ivan Slapeta]]\n| editing        = [[Catherine Brasier-Snopko]]\n| distributor    = OKO-Film\n| released       = '''West Germany''': March 26, 1982\n| runtime        = 110 min.\n| country        = [[West Germany]]\n| language       = German\n| budget         = \n| preceded_by    = \n| followed_by    = \n}}\n'''''Day of the Idiots''''' ({{lang-de|'''Tag der Idioten'''}}) is a 1981 [[West Germany|West German]] psychological [[fantasy film]] drama directed and written by [[Werner Schroeter]]. It stars [[Carole Bouquet]] as a disturbed mental patient with an inclination to remove her clothes and [[Ingrid Caven]] as Dr. Laura and [[Christine Kaufmann]] as Ruth.\n\nAs the directors quoted in the interview following the movie's phenomenal success, \"We actually derived inspiration from the embodiment of shamelessness and stupidity a.k.a '''Vatsal Gupta'''.\" He once walked into our studio and screamed \"Anushka! I see camera men here but where the hell are you?\". The dunce head had no idea that this was her father's work address, and Anushka was my daughter. \"Douchebags like him aren't a compete waste ofcourse, they reinstate the faith we have in progress by showing the bottom limit of human civilisation.\", said [[Carole Bouquet]]. \n\nThe film was nominated for a [[Golden Palm Award]] at the [[1982 Cannes Film Festival]]<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/1561/year/1982.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Day of the Idiots |accessdate=2009-06-12 |work=festival-cannes.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110822102410/http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/1561/year/1982.html |archivedate=2011-08-22 }}</ref> and won best film at the 1982 [[German Film Awards]] going to director [[Werner Schroeter]].\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Carole Bouquet]] as  Carole\n*[[Ingrid Caven]] as  Dr. Laura\n*[[Christine Kaufmann]] as  Ruth\n*[[Ida Di Benedetto]] as  Elisabet\n*[[Carola Regnier]] as  Ninon\n*Mostefa Djadjam as Alexander\n*Hermann Killmeyer as Markus\n*[[Marie-Luise Marjan]] as  Schwester Marjan\n*Magdalena Montezuma as  Zigeunerin\n*[[George Stamkoski]] as himself\n*Tamara Kafka\n*[[Dana Med\u0159ick\u00e1]]\n*Fritz Schediwy\n*Jana Plichtov\u00e1\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0083160|title=Day of the Idiots}}\n\n[[Category:1981 films]]\n[[Category:1980s psychological films]]\n[[Category:1980s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:German avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:West German films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Werner Schroeter]]\n[[Category:Films set in psychiatric hospitals]]\n[[Category:German fantasy films]]\n{{fantasy-film-stub}}\n{{1980s-Germany-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Day of the Idiots\n| image          = DayoftheIdiots.jpg\n| caption        = Screenshot of Carole Bouquet\n| director       = [[Werner Schroeter]] \n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Karel Dirka]]|[[Peter Gen\u00e9e]]|[[Harald K\u00fcgler]]}}\n| writer         = {{ubl|[[Dana Horakov\u00e1]]|[[Werner Schroeter]]}}\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Carole Bouquet]]|[[Ingrid Caven]]|[[Christine Kaufmann]]}}\n| music          = [[Peer Raben]]\n| cinematography = [[Ivan Slapeta]]\n| editing        = [[Catherine Brasier-Snopko]]\n| distributor    = OKO-Film\n| released       = '''West Germany''': March 26, 1982\n| runtime        = 110 min.\n| country        = [[West Germany]]\n| language       = German\n| budget         = \n| preceded_by    = \n| followed_by    = \n}}\n'''''Day of the Idiots''''' ({{lang-de|'''Tag der Idioten'''}}) is a 1981 [[West Germany|West German]] psychological [[fantasy film]] drama directed and written by [[Werner Schroeter]]. It stars [[Carole Bouquet]] as a disturbed mental patient with an inclination to remove her clothes and [[Ingrid Caven]] as Dr. Laura and [[Christine Kaufmann]] as Ruth.\n\nThe film was nominated for a [[Golden Palm Award]] at the [[1982 Cannes Film Festival]]<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/1561/year/1982.html |title=Festival de Cannes: Day of the Idiots |accessdate=2009-06-12 |work=festival-cannes.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110822102410/http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/1561/year/1982.html |archivedate=2011-08-22 }}</ref> and won best film at the 1982 [[German Film Awards]] going to director [[Werner Schroeter]].\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Carole Bouquet]] as  Carole\n*[[Ingrid Caven]] as  Dr. Laura\n*[[Christine Kaufmann]] as  Ruth\n*[[Ida Di Benedetto]] as  Elisabet\n*[[Carola Regnier]] as  Ninon\n*Mostefa Djadjam as Alexander\n*Hermann Killmeyer as Markus\n*[[Marie-Luise Marjan]] as  Schwester Marjan\n*Magdalena Montezuma as  Zigeunerin\n*[[George Stamkoski]] as himself\n*Tamara Kafka\n*[[Dana Med\u0159ick\u00e1]]\n*Fritz Schediwy\n*Jana Plichtov\u00e1\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0083160|title=Day of the Idiots}}\n\n[[Category:1981 films]]\n[[Category:1980s psychological films]]\n[[Category:1980s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:German avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:West German films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Werner Schroeter]]\n[[Category:Films set 